         <div type="translation" ana="#b1" xml:id="jeru0168.translation" corresp="#jeru0168.transcription">
            <p>Ashuni, son of Shim'on, son of Ashuni</p>
         </div>
      <div type="edition" subtype="transcription_segmented"><p><w xml:id="jeru0168-1" xml:lang="arc">אשוני</w> <w xml:id="jeru0168-2" xml:lang="arc">בר</w> <w xml:id="jeru0168-3" xml:lang="arc">שמעון</w> <w xml:id="jeru0168-4" xml:lang="arc">בר</w> <w xml:id="jeru0168-5" xml:lang="arc">אשוני</w> </p>
</div>
</body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Ossuary has yellow wash and low feet. Height describes that of chest plus that of vaulted lid. Ornamentation, on the chest's front side, consists of two metopes in zigzag frames, each containing a six-petalled rosette within a zigzag circle. Avigad compares the name אשוני to Talmudic אשיין and אשיאן, suggesting that it derives either from אישון, "pupil of the eye," or from אשן, "steadfast." Grandparents are infrequently mentioned.</p>
         </div>
